		"reset": "NOTE: Device reset will reset EEPROM, configuration parameters, Z-Wave chip and forcibly clear the Smart Water Valve’s Z-Wave Node Identification. Please use this procedure only when the network primary controller is missing or otherwise inoperable.\n\n1) Press and hold the NETWORKING button on the side of the control unit 5 seconds. The LEDs will blink rapidly for 5 seconds.\n2) If there are nodes in the “Lifeline” association group, the LEDs will blink slower until all nodes are notified using a Device Reset Locally Report.\n3) Once the device has been reset, the LEDs will return to their normal state.",
